headlines.description: — Joel Embiid played through an ankle injury to push his 30-10 streak to 13 games, finishing with 31 points and 10 rebounds in the Philadelphia 76ers’ 121-111 victory over the Toronto Raptors on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid plays through ankle injury to extend 30-10 streak to 13, 76ers beat Raptors 121-111

headlines.description: — Jamal Murray scored 32 points, Nikola Jokic had 29 points and 11 rebounds and the Denver Nuggets held off the Brooklyn Nets 122-117 on Friday night for their third straight victory.
headlines.shortLinkText: Murray, Jokic help defending champion Nuggets outlast Nets, 122-117

headlines.description: — Trae Young made some history. So did Duncan Robinson, and that was the difference for Miami.
headlines.shortLinkText: Herro, Robinson help Heat stave off Young and the Hawks, 122-113

headlines.description: — Alperen Sengun had 22 points and 15 rebounds and the Houston Rockets took advantage of the absence of injured Dallas stars Luka Doncic and Kyrie Irving to rout the Mavericks 122-96 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Sengun has 22 points and 15 rebounds to help Rockets rout Luka-less Mavericks 122-96

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 28 points, 12 assists and 11 rebounds for his fourth triple-double of the season and the Sacramento Kings beat the short-handed Phoenix Suns 120-105 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis has triple-double, Kings beat struggling Suns 120-105

events.name: Washington Wizards at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Stephen Curry and the Golden State starters were able to get off their legs for some extended rest down the stretch with another game in less than 24 hours.
headlines.shortLinkText: Stephen Curry outduels former teammate Jordan Poole to help Warriors beat Wizards, 129-118
